To convert markdown text to HTML, you can use the [Markdown](https://github.com/jgm/markdown) library. First, install the library using `cpp`. Then, you can write a function to convert markdown text to HTML using the library's `markdown` function.
```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include "markdown.h"

std::string markdownToHtml(const std::string& markdown) {
    markdown::Markdown markdown_;
    std::string html = markdown_.markdown(markdown);
    return html;
}

int main() {
    std::string markdown_text = "**Hello world!**";
    std::string html_text = markdownToHtml(markdown_text);
    std::cout << html_text << std::endl;
    return 0;
}
```
This function takes a reference to a `std::string` containing markdown formatted text and returns a `std::string` containing HTML formatted text. The `markdown` library is used to parse the markdown text and convert it to HTML.

